# the eza plugin does not SILENTLY fail if there is no eza installed,
# it actually aborts the zsh init process, and we will be locked out
# of our own system.
# so.
# this.
# (just to be DOUBLE careful, since this actually should no longer
# happen in practice, after we enabled the "brew" plugin for all
# systems)

command -v eza > /dev/null
